  "prompt": "How do I log in my Facebook account if you forgot your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Facebook password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page**: Open a web browser and go to the Facebook login page (www.facebook.com).\n\n2. **Click on \u2018Forgotten Password?\u2019**: Under the password field, click on the link that says \"Forgotten password?\"\n\n3. **Enter Your Information**: You\u2019ll be prompted to enter your email address or phone number associated with your account. After entering your information, click on \"Search.\"\n\n4. **Choose Your Recovery Option**: Facebook will show you options for receiving a code to reset your password. This could be via email or SMS, depending on what you have linked to your account. Select your preferred option and click \"Continue.\"\n\n5. **Retrieve the Code**: Check your email or SMS for the code sent by Facebook. \n\n6. **Enter the Code**: Go back to the Facebook page and enter the code in the provided field.\n\n7. **Set a New Password**: After entering the code, you will be prompted to create a new password. Make sure it\u2019s strong and not similar to your previous passwords.\n\n8. **Log In**: Once you\u2019ve set your new password, you can log in to your account using your email/phone number and the new password.\n\n9. **Review Account Security**: After regaining access, it's a good idea to check your security settings to ensure your account is secure. You might want to enable two-factor authentication for added security.\n\nIf you don't receive the code or have trouble accessing your email or phone, you can follow the additional prompts on Facebook to verify your identity and recover your account.",
